      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"rigged\" game is the only one where you actually have a hand to play, so the struggle is the only thing that proves you were ever there. If the end is zero, then the only way to make the journey meaningful is to stop trying to change the score and start focusing on the beauty of the final moments. Why endure the agonizing climb when you could simply sit down and watch the sunset, knowing it's the last time you'll see it?",
